# Assistant rules for this workspace

- Always use absolute imports starting with "@/..." for files under `src`; never "./" or "../".
- Apply these rules only to the file(s) currently being edited; do not scan or change other files.
- Convert existing relative imports to "@/..." within the current edit file only.
- Prefer updating nearby imports in the same file for consistency; avoid cross-file edits.

# File Naming Rules

- When creating new files, always use lowercase letters.
- Separate words with dashes (-).
- Example filenames:
  - file-component.tsx
  - user-profile-card.tsx
  - login-form.tsx
